OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778883107
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FSymptoms of meningitis can look
OL,7,Fsimilar to common illnesses like a
OL,8,Fcold or flu; however, someone with
OL,9,Fmeningitis will usually become
OL,10,Fseriously ill in a matter of hours.
OL,12,FSymptoms can include fever, seizures,
OL,13,Fvomiting, headache, a stiff neck, or a
OL,14,Frash that does not fade when a glass
OL,15,Fis pressed against it.
OL,17,FSome people may also become drowsy,
OL,18,Funresponsive or sensitive to bright
OL,19,Flights.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778883107
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FSymptoms can appear in any order and
OL,7,Fmay not always be present at once.
OL,9,FThe UK Health Security Agency advises
OL,10,Fcalling 999 immediately or going to
OL,11,Fyour nearest A&E if you think you or
OL,12,Fsomeone in your care could have
OL,13,Fmeningitis or septicaemia, as people
OL,14,Fcan become unwell very quickly.
OL,16,FYou can call NHS 111 if you're unsure
OL,17,Fwhether it's serious.
OL,19,FWhat causes meningitis, and how does
OL,20,Fit spread?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
