CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778883107
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,7,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,8,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,9,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,11,FIs there a vaccine for meningitis, and
OL,12,Fhow do I know if I've had one?
OL,14,FSeveral vaccines protect against
OL,15,Fdifferent meningococcal groups,
OL,16,Fincluding MenB and MenACWY. Other
OL,17,Froutine childhood vaccines, such as
OL,18,Fthe 6-in-1 vaccine and MMR, protect
OL,19,Fagainst infections that can also cause
OL,20,Fmeningitis.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31413
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778883107
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FThe pneumococcal vaccine is offered to
OL,7,Fbabies in two doses or a single dose
OL,8,Fto adults aged 65 or over.
OL,10,FTeenagers, sixth formers and freshers
OL,11,Fattending university for the first
OL,12,Ftime can have the MenACWY vaccine,
OL,13,Fwhich can help protect against
OL,14,Fmeningitis and sepsis.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31414
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778883107
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,F"Vaccination remains the best
OL,7,Fprotection. The MenACWY and MenB
OL,8,Fvaccines used in the UK are safe,
OL,9,Fwelltested, and available free to
OL,10,Feligible UK and international
OL,11,Fstudents," said Dr Simon Clarke,
OL,12,FAssociate Professor of Cellular
OL,13,FMicrobiology, University of Reading.
OL,15,FThe MenACWY vaccine can be given up to
OL,16,Fthe age of 25 if it has been missed
OL,17,Fand is also available to some
OL,18,Findividuals who are at greater risk
OL,19,Fdue to a medical condition, work,
OL,20,Ftravel or close contact with someone
OL,21,Fwho is infected.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31415
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778883107
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FWhile the NHS offers vaccinations to
OL,7,Fthose most at risk, private
OL,8,Fvaccinations are available at some
OL,9,Ftravel clinics, private GP practices
OL,10,Fand pharmacies.
OL,12,FFor the particular strain identified
OL,13,Fin the Kent outbreak, the MenB vaccine
OL,14,Fis the best protection.
OL,16,FHowever, as Dr Alfahl says: "many
OL,17,Fcurrent university students were born
OL,18,Fbefore the infant MenB programme began
OL,19,Fin 2015, which means some of them may
OL,20,Fnever have been routinely offered that
OL,21,Fvaccine."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31416
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778883107
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FIf you are unsure if you or your child
OL,7,Fhas been vaccinated, you can speak to
OL,8,Fyour GP.
OL,10,FShould I be getting the MenB vaccine?
OL,12,FThe government are not currently
OL,13,Fadvising people to pay for private
OL,14,Fvaccinations.
OL,16,FThe MenB vaccine is offered by some
OL,17,Fprivate pharmacies; however, they are
OL,18,Fwarning of shortages.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31417
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778883107
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FStreeting said that the government is
OL,7,Fcurrently seeking advice from the
OL,8,FJCVI, an independent body of
OL,9,Fscientists who make recommendations to
OL,10,Fthe government, to look at what has
OL,11,Fhappened in Canterbury and issue fresh
OL,12,Fadvice.
OL,14,FWhat other ways can I help protect
OL,15,Fmyself from meningitis?
OL,17,FAvoid sharing items which come into
OL,18,Fcontact with your mouth, such as food
OL,19,Fand eating utensils.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31418
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778883107
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FDrinks and vapes are also best kept to
OL,7,Fone person to help prevent spread.
OL,9,FFollowing the recent outbreak, GPs
OL,10,Facross the country have now been told
OL,11,Fto prescribe antibiotics to anyone who
OL,12,Fvisited a nightclub in Canterbury from
OL,13,FMarch 5-7, plus students from the
OL,14,FUniversity of Kent.
OL,16,FHow is meningitis treated?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31419
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778883107
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FPeople with suspected meningitis may
OL,7,Fhave to have hospital tests to get a
OL,8,Fdiagnosis and find out if their
OL,9,Fillness is a viral or bacterial
OL,10,Finfection.
OL,12,FBacterial meningitis usually requires
OL,13,Fhospital treatment for at least a
OL,14,Fweek, including antibiotics, fluids
OL,15,Fand oxygen.
OL,17,FShould students be especially careful?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31420
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778883107
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FAccess to vaccinations has meant
OL,7,Foutbreaks are more unusual; however,
OL,8,Fmeningitis can spread rapidly in
OL,9,Fplaces like universities and colleges.
OL,11,FTom Nutt, chief executive of
OL,12,FMeningitis Now, says: "University
OL,13,Fstudents and young adults are among
OL,14,Fthe groups at increased risk because
OL,15,Fmeningitis bacteria can spread more
OL,16,Feasily in settings where people live,
OL,17,Fstudy and socialise closely together."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G20/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31421
SC,0021
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778883107
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FTrish Mannes, UKHSA regional deputy
OL,7,Fdirector for the South East, adds:
OL,8,F"Students are particularly at risk of
OL,9,Fmissing the early warning signs of
OL,10,Fmeningitis because they can be easily
OL,11,Fconfused with other illnesses such as
OL,12,Fa bad cold, flu or even a hangover.
OL,14,F"That's why it's vital that, if a
OL,15,Ffriend goes to bed unwell, you check
OL,16,Fon them regularly and don't hesitate
OL,17,Fto seek medical help by contacting
OL,18,Ftheir GP or calling NHS 111 if they
OL,19,Fhave these symptoms or you're
OL,20,Fconcerned about them. This could save
OL,21,Ftheir life."
OL,26,@pD@AOUvD@AOU}D@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G21/22
